Stakeholders have tasked businesses to speedily innovate through effective collaboration and creation of standardised platforms to accelerate digital transformation, aimed at co-creating with other companies to rapidly develop and scale new solutions. Speaking at the 2019 KPMG Digital Summit, in Lagos, on Tuesday, they argued that technology-driven ideas are pivotal to developing strong and productive relationships among companies, from providing communication tools to using new systems like augmented reality to enable businesses to share their expertise.
  
Furthermore, they added that digital transformation can help by creating standardised platforms to share data seamlessly and increase collaboration.
  
Specifically, the Head of the AI & Cognitive Practice at KPMG Israel Data & Analytics Department, Rolan Kab, said to create successful transformation process, there is a need for different alignment and collaborative processes to occur.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .